= News:

- Golnaz was selected for an interview at The Hartwell Foundation for a New Investigator Award.

- John Johnson (IGG PhD Student) rotated in our lab on May 2015. It only took 17 months until he finally joined the lab (in co-mentorship with John Wherry). Welcome JJ!

- Steph Sansbury joined the lab as a GGR rotation student. Welcome Steph!

- Dr. George Georgakilias an expert in micro-RNA analysis joined our lab in August 2016. Welcome George!

- Aaron Chen joined our lab as a research specialist. Welcome Aaron! 

- The Vahedi laboratory is the recipient of Discovery Grant from the [https://www.psoriasis.org National Psoriasis Foundation]. 

- Dr. Vahedi was invited to a panel at [https://www.training.nih.gov/assets/2016_Career_Symposium_Program.pdf the NIH Career Symposium].

- Congratulations to my first two IGG rotation students Jacob Paiano and John Johnson. Jacob was awarded the National Science Foundation Graduate Research Fellowship and John Johnson received an honorable mention. 

- Dr. Vahedi received the prestigous [http://www.sloan.org/fellowships/2016-sloan-research-fellows Alfred P. Sloan Fellowship in Computational and Evolutionary Molecular Biology] in February 2016 ([http://www.uphs.upenn.edu/news/News_Releases/2016/02/sloan/ The Penn News announcement)].

- Our super-enhancer study in T cells as [http://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/2015-insights-lab the NIH's 2015 Research Highlights]. 

- Dr. Vahedi's seminar at the 4th International Conference on Immunotherapy in 
Pediatric Oncology (CIPO2015) in September 2015 can be watched [https://youtu.be/wcNO3nCCo9E here].

- IGG rotation students, John and Jacob, published a commentary in [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26444855 European Jounal of Immunology] in October 2015.

- Dr. Vahedi receives Pfizer's 2015 ASPIRE US Rheumatology and Dermatology competitive research grant award for the proposal “Epigenomic Mapping of Psoriasis”. 

- Dr. Vahedi is the recipient of 2015's NIH Director's Award in "recognition of exceptional productivity and scientific contributions to genetic immunology research" in the NIAMS intramural program.

